the new sharing revolution events at stanford the new sharing revolution facebook twitter email print add to calendar social ties are one of the major predictors for health but in our frenetic culture people have less time for others social discourse is on the decline with rudeness and anger increasing we need to find ways to bring people together in collaborative and cooperative ways the new sharing revolution is bringing people together to share for mutual benefit this new cooperative movement helps people build community and use fewer resources benefitting the overall health of both people and the planet people are involved in sharing cars houses and working areas they re engaged in co housing time banks lending clubs and local projects that share tools exchange food produce and even gardening space in this workshop people will learn about the many opportunities for sharing and how they can get involved in this movement in a way that helps reduce stress by increasing social ties and saving money in particular people will learn specific techniques of conversation and social engagement that increases cooperation and collaboration instructor cecile andrews edd author of the books slow is beautiful circle of simplicity and less is more when thursday november 3 2011 5 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where medical school office bld msob rm 303 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public members tags class humanities public service health wellness sponsor health improvement program contact 650 721 6003 ausserer stanford edu admission register for this class at hip stanford edu class fee $35 class code nsr 01 stap ea funds yes permalink http events stanford edu events 295 29507 more info last modified october 19 2011
